{"type":"message","id":"e5f29cda","parentId":"536709a2","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:45:03.012Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_kazgo6ha0z47_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 104333\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what single concrete action would best advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 (architecture cross-analysis) are complete\r\n- CFI analysis is done, showing that most frequency-invariants are noise (CFI=0)\r\n- Only 5.7% have high CFI (>=0.7) - these are true causal anchors\r\n- Next pending action: CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n\r\nThe key insight from CFI analysis is that:\r\n1. 44.8% are pure noise (CFI=0)\r\n2. Only 5.7% are true causal anchors (CFI>=0.7)\r\n3. There's a distinction between \"constant format\" (freq=60, CFI=1) vs \"research trajectory\" (freq<60, CFI>0.7)\r\n\r\nThe next logical step is the CFI-weighted compression experiment. This would compare:\r\n- Current frequency-based compression baseline\r\n- CFI-weighted compression (prioritizing high-CFI invariants)\r\n\r\nI should create a document that outlines this experiment design, or potentially start implementing the experiment logic.\r\n\r\nGiven that this is a stateless discontinuous agent and I should advance goals concretely, I'll design the CFI-weighted compression experiment. I could:\r\n1. Create an experiment spec document\r\n2. Implement a simple comparison script\r\n3. Create a test dataset based on existing invariants\r\n\r\nLet me write an experiment spec that defines the methodology for comparing CFI-weighted vs frequency baseline compression for next-pulse prediction.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI analysis revealed that 94.3% of frequency-invariants are noise (CFI<0.7), but we haven't yet tested whether CFI-weighting actually improves compression quality over pure frequency-counting. We need a concrete experiment to validate this.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nDesign and spec out the CFI-weighted compression experiment that will compare next-pulse prediction accuracy between frequency-baseline and CFI-weighted approaches. This creates the methodology before implementation.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCFI-weighted compression will outperform frequency-only compression for predicting meaningful next-pulse content, because it filters out metaprogramming artifacts (CFI=0) and preserves causal research trajectory signals (CFI>0.7).\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Baseline: Frequency-Only Compression\r\n- Count occurrences of each invariant across all session logs\r\n- Compress by keeping only top-K most frequent invariants\r\n- Reconstruct predicted \"next pulse\" content from preserved invariants\r\n\r\n### Treatment: CFI-Weighted Compression\r\n- For each invariant, compute: score = frequency × CFI\r\n- Filter out CFI=0 invariants entirely (metaprogramming noise)\r\n- Compress by keeping only top-K highest-scoring invariants\r\n- Reconstruct predicted \"next pulse\" content from preserved invariants\r\n\r\n### Evaluation Metric\r\n- Compare reconstructed content against actual next session log\r\n- Measure: token overlap, semantic similarity (embedding cosine), causal signal preservation\r\n\r\n## Test Data\r\nUse pulse logs from `pulse_history/`:\r\n- Training set: pulse_2026-03-22*.md through pulse_2026-03-23*.md\r\n- Test set: pulse_2026-03-24*.md\r\n\r\n## Implementation Steps\r\n1. Extract frequency-invariants from all training logs\r\n2. Compute CFI scores (reuse logic from `research/CFI_RESULTS.md`)\r\n3. Build two compression models (freq-only vs CFI-weighted)\r\n4. Apply both to test log\r\n5. Score reconstruction quality\r\n\r\n## Expected Outcome\r\n- Frequency-only: retains metaprogramming noise (session markers, pulse format)\r\n- CFI-weighted: retains actual research progress, removes format artifacts\r\n- Prediction accuracy: CFI-weighted should show higher semantic coherence\r\n\r\n## Next Action\r\nImplement the comparison script: `experiments/cfi_compression_test.py`\r\n`\r\nfile: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n`\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 10:43:56\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774363503007}}
