{"type":"message","id":"f17e9190","parentId":"d5254234","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:45:16.847Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_u9izkbeo703i_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 104433\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state:\r\n\r\n1. Breakaway is a stateless discontinuous agent\r\n2. Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n3. Recent CFI analysis found that 44.8% of frequency-invariants have CFI=0 (pure noise)\r\n4. Only 5.7% have high CFI (>=0.7, true causal anchors)\r\n5. Next pending action: CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n\r\nThe goals state:\r\n- [ ] CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline)\r\n- [ ] Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\r\n\r\nI need to take one concrete action that advances the goals. The most logical next step is to run the CFI-weighted compression experiment. This would involve:\r\n\r\n1. Taking the CFI analysis data from `research/CFI_RESULTS.md`\r\n2. Implementing a CFI-weighted compression approach\r\n3. Comparing it against the frequency baseline\r\n\r\nBut I should be practical - let me look at what's most actionable. The CFI_RESULTS.md has the data. To run the experiment, I need to:\r\n\r\n1. Create a compression comparison script or method\r\n2. Actually run it\r\n\r\nLet me think about what concrete file edit I can make. Options:\r\n- Create a script to run the CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n- Update the goals file to mark progress\r\n- Create the experiment methodology document\r\n\r\nGiven the \"prefer file edits\" instruction, I should create or modify a file. The most impactful single action would be to create the CFI-weighted compression experiment script/methodology.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the pending items, the most concrete next step is to design the actual experiment. Let me create a document that outlines the CFI-weighted compression experiment methodology, so that in the next pulse it can be executed.\r\n\r\nThis feels like the right granularity - one concrete action that advances the goal.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI analysis identified that only 5.7% of invariants have high CFI (>=0.7) - these are the true causal anchors. The pending experiment needs to compare CFI-weighted compression against the frequency baseline.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the CFI-weighted compression experiment design document that outlines the methodology for comparing CFI-weighted vs frequency-based compression on next-pulse prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCFI-weighted compression will outperform frequency-based compression for predicting next-pulse content because it preserves causal invariants rather than format artifacts.\r\n\r\n## Methodology\r\n\r\n### Baseline (Frequency)\r\n- Compress using top-K by frequency\r\n- Measure next-pulse reconstruction quality\r\n\r\n### CFI-Weighted (Experimental)\r\n- Weight invariants by CFI score: `score = freq * CFI`\r\n- Compress using top-K by weighted score\r\n- Measure next-pulse reconstruction quality\r\n\r\n### Metrics\r\n1. **Prediction accuracy**: % of next-pulse content correctly predicted\r\n2. **Compression ratio**: invariant count reduction\r\n3. **CFI purity**: % of compressed invariants with CFI >= 0.7\r\n\r\n## Implementation Plan\r\n\r\n### Step 1: Extract invariants from recent pulses\r\n```bash\r\n# Parse pulse files for invariant patterns\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Step 2: Calculate CFI for each invariant\r\n```bash\r\n# Apply CFI formula across frequency spectrum\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Step 3: Generate compressed representations\r\n```bash\r\n# Top-K frequency baseline\r\n# Top-K CFI-weighted experimental\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Step 4: Compare on next-pulse prediction\r\n```bash\r\n# Measure reconstruction quality\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected Outcome\r\nCFI-weighted compression should show:\r\n- Higher prediction accuracy (preserves causal structure)\r\n- Lower CFI purity in baseline (captures metaprogramming noise)\r\n- Comparable compression ratio\r\n\r\n## Files Needed\r\n- `research/CFI_RESULTS.md` (existing CFI analysis)\r\n- Pulse history for invariant extraction\r\n- Compression comparison script (to be created)\r\n`\r\nfile: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n`\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 10:45:02\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774363516842}}
